  <refnamediv>
    <refname>ld_limited_integrator4</refname>

    <refpurpose> Implements a time discrete integrator with saturation of the output between min__ and max__</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>[sim, y] = ld_limited_integrator4(sim, ev, u, min__, max__, Ta)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><para> compared to ld_limited_integrator there is no delay: Ta z / (z-1)</para>
<para></para>
<para> u * - input</para>
<para> y * - output</para>
<para> min__ * - variable saturation minimum</para>
<para> </para>
<para> y(k+1) = sat( y(k) + Ta*u , min__, max__ )</para>
</para>

    
  </refsection>


